accessrestrict.p: Series 1, 2, 4, and 5 are closed to research for 25 years from date of record creation.

acqinfo.p: Materials acquired through transfers from the Office of Sponsored Research.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Sponsored Research Office is now part of the Associate Vice President for Research & Graduate Studies. The Office of Research Services (ORS) was created to support the efforts of the GW community to generate and manage external awards in support of research, training, instruction, and public service activities. ORS works with investigators in every University component to decipher and adhere to University and sponsor regulations, while reducing time spent on the administrative aspects of sponsored activities. ORS is the University office designated to represent the University in providing the final institutional signature on proposals, in negotiating terms and conditions for grants, contracts, subcontracts, and other award mechanisms, and in dealing with administrative representatives of external sponsors on issues related to sponsored programs.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of government contract projects with the U.S. Navy, logistics technical project reports, contracting manuals, sponsored research project files from various schools, departments, and programs (including the School of Education, School of Engineering, Medical School, National Law Center, Institute for Educational Leadership, Social Research Group, Education Research Project, and logistics), lists of sponsored research awards, Allegany Ballistics Laboratory project files, and reports of the Human Resources Research Organization (HUMRRO). They range in date from 1942 to 1996, and were transferred to the University Archives by the Director of the Department of Sponsored Research. Note: Not all series are processed. Ask staff for assistance.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into ten series: Government contract projects; Logistics projects reports; Manuals and programs; Project files for schools, departments, programs; Project files for programs and institutes; Lists of sponsored research awards; Alleghany ballistic laboratory project files; Human Resources Research Organization (HUMRRO); Research records; and Photos of the Alleghany research project.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of government contract projects with the U.S. Navy. These include reports and contracts with individual shipyards, such as Boston, Charleston, Long Beach, Pearl Harbor, and San Francisco, as well as individual ships in various naval fleets, forces, and naval bases. Their arrangement is predominantly chronological by subject at the beginning and then by subject at the end. The material dates from 1952-1957, and were transferred to the University Archives by the Director of Sponsored Research in 1990.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of logistics technical project reports. Their arrangement is chronological by report number. The series also includes monthly progress reports, employee/salary lists, and interviews. The material dates from the 1950's and was transferred to the University Archives by the Director of Sponsored Research in 1987.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of cost reimbursement contracting manuals, and a program for the 10th Annual Government Contracts Institute at George Washington University. They are arranged chronologically. The material dates from 1963-77, and was accessioned as part of project to clear the backlog in 2001.
This series has a container list in electronic form, please ask staff for assistance.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of files from the Allegany Ballistics Laboratory, which researched and developed missiles for the U.S. government during World War II. Materials include memos, correspondence, flight test reports, drawings, blueprints, and part of a missile housing. It also includes files from the Human Resources Research Office (HUMRRO). They are arranged alphabetically by subject files. The materials range in date from 1942-47, and were transferred to University Archives by the Director of Sponsored Research in 2000.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of materials from the Human Resources Research Organization (HUMRRO). These include publications, annual reports, bibliographies, and research reports. scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains reports, correspondence, handbooks, press releases, organization chart, memorandums, agreements, lease, bibliographies, photograph, newsletters, brochures, posters, proposal, and a Congressional Record. They range in date from 1946 to 1996. The material concern annual reports, strategies, sponsored research, the Office of Scientific Research and Development, ballistics, policies, procedures, the Human Resources Research Office (HumRRO), the Human Resources Research Organization (HumRRO), research, the Cooperative Education and Training Program, the Technical Education Center, separation of HumRRO from George Washington University, Raymond L. Bishplinghoff, patent policy, the Program of Policy Studies in Science and Technology, sourses of science and society, research support, grants, Innovation Information nd Analysis Project, nuclear energy, Innovation Information Center, obstacles to research, committee reports, the Interagency Panels on Early Childhood Research and Development, National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), Biological Sciences Communication Project, Center for Manpower Policy Studies, employment, staff, First Federal Congress Publications Project, Languages of the World Archive, Mid-Atlantic Regional Resource Center (MARRC), population research, National Endowment for the Humanities award for a humanities development program, and Eric Clearinghouse for Higher Education.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
